if (true) {
```

Actually the placeholder IS the `if (typeof s === 'function')` line. So `var s = arguments[i]` must be declared elsewhere or... it's declared by the placeholder too.

Given the mutation changes `if (typeof s === 'function')` to `if (true)`, when we pass an object with `.sink` and `.source`, the mutated code will try to call `s(read)` (treating the object as a function), which will throw a TypeError.

